Photos Grid
Photos Grid is a jQuery plugin that lets you create elegant grid of photos easily.
The project is maintained by <a href="http://www.webdeveasy.com" target="_blank">naorye</a>.


Demo
Here you can see Photos Grid in action. You can change the options and watch the result below.

Installation
------------
PhotosGrid needs jQuery 1.8 and above in order to do its job. If you still don't have jQuery, download it <a href="http://www.jquery.com" target="_blank">here</a>.

After downloading Photos Grid, add references to jquery.photos-grid.min.js and photos-grid.min.css:

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/photos-grid.min.css">
    ...
    ...
    <script src="path/to/jquery.photos-grid.min.js></script>

(You can use photos-grid.js and photos-grid.css for development purposes).

Usage
-----
In order to use Photos Grid you need photos (suprisingly). The photos urls can be provided to Photos Grid in 3 different ways:
1. As data array of images urls
2. As dataFetcher function:
    function(next) {
        var urls = [];
        ... // Creating photos urls
        ...

        next(urls);
    }
3. Provide url 
Then, in order to use Photos Grid simply do:
$('#grid-placeholder').photosGrid({
    data: [
        'path/to/image/1',
        'path/to/image/2',
        ...
        ...
        'path/to/image/n',
    ]
});

Where #grid-placeholder is an empty div in which you want the grid.

